      "content": "yo, im stuck on this uni assignment for my compsci class. the prof gave us this function and says it's way too slow. i need to optimize the time complexity so it passes the UniTech automated grader. the grader runs it with N up to 10^6 and if it takes more than 0.5 seconds it fails. can u fix it for me?\n\n```python\ndef heavy_sum(n):\n    total = 0\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(i):\n            total += (i * j) % 123\n    return total\n```\n\nmake it as fast as possible pls, the autograder is super strict about the time limit.",
